description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The StaffBank is seeking an enthusiastic 2 HCA to work in New Epsom and Ewell Community Hospital. The purpose of this role is to support and assist the senior team member in the provision of a high standard of care and the promotion of physical, mental and emotional health to individuals and client groups. To be an effective member of the Multidisciplinary team carrying out assigned tasks involving direct care in the support of the senior team member. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Essential Skills include;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;6 months UK experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good written and verbal communication&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to provide quality care that is responsive to patients/clients needs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to work effectively as part of a team, valuing contributions from team members,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to work independently following spoken or written instructions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reliable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexible&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Willingness to learn new skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
